14/09/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- State department spokesman Adam Ereli welcomed last week's apologies by Croatian President Stipe Mesic and his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Svetozar Marovic, for their countries' wrongdoings during the wars in the former Yugoslavia. Ereli said Friday (12 September) that the apologies and actions taken to resolve open issues should contribute to normalising bilateral ties and stability in the region. (HINA, MIA, PBS BiH, BBC - 13/09/03)
